history.content: If you're working in a Soda lab, your faculty or grad student can work with the front desk to get you access. If you're not in classes and you're not associated with a lab, you will not have special access

After the Spring 2018 semester ended I no longer had off-hours access to Soda, and beginning this week I no longer have access to (and in) Cory. (I'm an EECS major.)

Is this supposed to happen? I'm not enrolled in any classes, but I still spend a lot of my own time in Cory working on affiliated research. @961 explains the current situation, but I was just wondering if anything's changed.
